This paper is about improving the efficiency of training deep neural networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on neural networks and machine learning, as well as the use of various deep learning architectures and datasets in the experiments, it is most likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also deals with computer vision tasks, such as image classification, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these fields are all relevant to the study of deep learning and optimization.
